texts.text: >The Liberators struggle in the face of Shaddai's power.
Geez, how strong is this thing...
We didn't actually resort to fighting the other day...
But it seems no different from the other Godly spirits in terms of power.
Yo, what do we do...?
You appear to be at your limit.
Yet you wish to keep fighting.
Yeah, we ain't givin' up!
Then how about...?
This!
*Squeal*
*Whimper*
No, my demons!
Now, Liberators, pray.
Pray for salvation at the edge of despair.
Return to the righteous path and obey God's will as his true children.
No way! We ain't gonna be able to protect people by bein' your puppets!
Yo, us humans are gonna decide how we're gonna save this world!
You humans are weak.
But if you keep insisting that your will is that strong,
then there you leave me with no other choice.
>A tremendous amount of light begins gathering upon Shaddai.
It's too bright. I can't see...!
Yo, what the hell's goin' on?!
Are we finally getting erased?
Dammit...!

This is bad.
There's no stopping it now!
*Roar*
>Just as you all begin to believe that this is the end...
That will be more than enough, Shaddai.
>As a sublime voice echoes, you all look to the sky.
>Elohim makes its descent while being wreathed in divine light.
I see that you have recovered from your last battle, Elohim.
Judgment has already been passed, Shaddai.
We relinquished the final decision to Sabaoth, did we not?
Sabaoth's decision is God's decision.
Do you wish to be like them?
You do not wish to erase anymore, Elohim?
What's going on here?
Who's "them"?
Now that you are all gathered...
Liberators, allow me to discuss my decision once more.
This world is doomed to be destroyed by Vanitas. The end is indeed nigh.
We have seen countless worlds be destroyed by it up until this point.
And it is a simple fact that you humans have been at the center of the calamity each and every time.
Returning you humans to a more righteous path by recreating this world...
Fundamentally, Elohim is not wrong.
It matters not how many of God's creations vanish.
Say what?!

Yo, hold up...
What happened to us passing your stupid trial...?!
I am in agreement with Elohim and Shaddai.
I understand their reasoning.
However, you humans have proved to me otherwise.
Liberators, you have shown me your power.
Use that power to fight against Vanitas...
Use that power to deal with that unholy monstrosity once and for all.
Then, you will be spared from being erased.
Deal with Vanitas...
Yo, Sabaoth, you don't have to tell us. We're gonna do that no matter what.
We're gonna protect our world.
We appreciate you actually sayin' that you're not gonna erase us...
But that still leaves a few questions unanswered.
Based on what you just said, Vanitas is also a huge thorn in your side.
Why aren't you doing anything about it?
Why is it that you need us, humans that you clearly consider to be weak,
to defeat it on our own like this?
She's right. Why is that?
Wouldn't it be easier if all of you just dealt with it?
Ah, you still do not understand.
Yes, we can indeed handle it on our own with ease...
But it is just like us. A part of God.
Vanitas is another one of you?!
Yo, seriously?!
I speak only the truth. It is another part of God.
It escaped his grasp and has been rampaging about...
God will surely agree with us when it comes to this.
We came here to test you to see if you have the power to defeat Vanitas,
and our trials showed us that you are indeed capable.
But that also means Elohim and Shaddai had different goals in mind.
You defeated Elohim. There is no denying that.
And so, I shall deem you worthy.
Humans, as the Lord of the Armies,
in the name of God, you are to be rid of Vanitas.
Hah!
That's just another way of calling us useful soldiers.
I agree.
You're just recruiting us into your army, no, your lordship?
And you're willing to keep us alive as long as we're fighting against Vanitas, right?
Are we wrong?
And if that is the case?
You should feel proud of being given this honor.
Take that pride and fight valiantly in your struggle.
Based on how you do, I may even bestow upon you the honor of joining my own army.
Yo, some honor that is...
So this is God...
Man, it's not even worth arguing against them...
>You are all left speechless by its sheer arrogance.
>Then, Elohim begins floating into the air.
If it means being rid of Vanitas once and for all, then I have no choice.
I will not erase you.
The destruction of this world can wait until another time.
What? You still plan on actually going through with that?
Humans.
You said that you wish to free your brethren from this malice.
Believe in God, spread the word and remain righteous.
Faith will foster the connections you seek.
Believe in him. Believe in his power...
>Elohim rises into the sky and it vanishes along with its glow.
I also accept Sabaoth's decision.
However, Liberators, you are to never defy the will of God...
Your punishment will be beyond severe if you do indeed act in such a manner.
Remain true and faithful...
Shaddai...
>Shaddai also begins rising into the air and follows Elohim by vanishing.
>Only Sabaoth remains and continues to eye the Liberators...
Defeat Vanitas and save this world.
But if the end result does not please us...
If it doesn't please you...?
Stay righteous, Liberators...
>All of the Godly spirits have gone...
>Their sublime voices no longer echo throughout the city.
>The sky over Tokyo returns to being nighttime.

*Sigh*
I'm completely exhausted...
Me too...
We did spend the entire day fighting...
And everything they said at the very end...
I'm guessing it took the wind out of all of us.
Yes, we're going to need quite some time to process this information...
Those no-good-for-nothing balls of light just do as they please...
>Talking is becoming a challenge at this point.
>So is standing as pure exhaustion sets in.
>All the Liberators can do now is take turns sighing.
I was under the belief that Shaddai was much more understanding than Elohim.
But I couldn't have been more wrong.
It took me by complete surprise,
God really does work in mysterious ways.
Yo, ain't that the truth.
Sabaoth wants us to be its soldiers.
Elohim just wants to erase everythin' in sight.
And Shaddai's the ultimate control freak.
All we want to do is save all these folks and free them from this malice, yo...
It's like we gotta carry all this extra weight on top of that now.
Yeah, I totally get that.
They might end up being worse than Vanitas, you know?
Yeah, especially that part about not pickin' a fight with God...
But we don't need them to like us or anythin' like that.
We just gotta do what we can to save this world.
And our "Fellowship" is gonna give us a fightin' chance.
It's all startin' to come together now.
Right, Vince? Honey?
Right! Nobody can beat us when we're together!
But don't forget that we used to be the bad guys. Talk about irony.
Yo, none of that matters anymore.
We're all in this together. As the Liberators.
We're all aimin' for the same goal now.
Anyway, there ain't no point in stickin' around here any more than we have to.
Just a little more and we'll be on our way home.

*Groan*
I'm starving...
Whatever we end up eating today's gonna be amazing no matter what.
Or you could just keep burning calories until you die.

*Wince*
I guess my trial hasn't ended yet...
>You head towards the elevator as you chat with one another...
>However...
Huh?
Uh oh...
Is something wrong, Ririn?
Bad news, guys...
The buttons still aren't working.
What?
There's still no power...
None of them are on...!!!
You're joking, right?! We have to walk all the way down?!
No, God, help us...!
You're saying that now...?
Still, my knees are gonna give out before this world does...
>The Liberators' shouting can be heard through the city...
